New Records: Nikola Jokic had a near triple-double with 46 points, 10 rebounds, and 10 assists in the overtime victory.
Key Match Events: Nikola Jokic had 46 points and 10 rebounds, and the Denver Nuggets beat the San Antonio Spurs 122-111 in overtime to spoil Victor Wembanyama's 21st birthday.
Victor Wembanyama had 23 rebounds in the loss.
Post-Match Reflections: Nikola Jokic and the Denver Nuggets spoiled Victor Wembanyama's 21st birthday on Saturday.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played on January 5, 2025, at the Frost Bank Center in San Antonio, TX, with an attendance of 19,038.
The Denver Nuggets and San Antonio Spurs are tied 1-1 in the regular season series.
Others: The game was played in overtime, with the Nuggets winning 122-111.
The Spurs' Victor Wembanyama had a big game with 23 rebounds and a highlight-reel alley-oop slam.
